				<td colspan="2" height="100%" valign="top"><span class="postbody"><img align="right" valign="top" src="http://images.google.com/images?q=tbn:sW-lVTG4Q8gJ:www.0800sexshop.com/images/1235%2520out%2520of%2520stock.jpg">Blizzard just stuffed a ball-gag into the mouths of people who had been dogging PVP as a waste of time due to rank decay. Check this forum post:
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Fangtooth wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
1.6 Addition | 6/27/2005 6:51:36 PM PDT           
<br />

<br />
Honor system reward item’s rank requirement will now be based on a characters highest lifetime rank rather than the character’s current rank.  
<br />
 (<a href="http://forums.worldofwarcraft.com/thread.aspx?FN=wow-general&T=3782632&P=1">source</a>)</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
PVP participation will go up across the board as a result of this change. It's huge!
<br />

<br />
The cynic in me says that they've done this because they're further behind in development of PVE content than they reckoned they would be and that they need SOMETHING to mop up all the spare time their level 60 players have. 
<br />

<br />
In the short run, this change will mean many more players participating in PVP as everyone attempts to achieve a high rank for gear. If you're a more casual player, now is NOT the time to jump into PVP, as you'll be competing for rank with just about everyone else.
<br />

<br />
In the long run, this change will accellerate game mudflation. Overall, it has become easier to obtain gear. This buys the company a few months to make detailed announcements about a significant PVE expansion.</span><br /><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
