				<td colspan="2" height="100%" valign="top"><span class="postbody">Some interesting math:
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">My guild (Conquest) started raiding Molten Core on January 3rd of this year. From that time until April 29th (the day we killed Ragnaros) we raided EVERY single day 6 hours a night. That is 116 days of raiding 6 hours a night. That is 696 hours before we killed Ragnaros for the first time. Since then we have been raiding twice a week to clear MC about 4 hours a day. So 8 hours a week from April 29th to June 27th. 8 weeks at 8 hours a week is 64 hours. Add that to the 696 hours we spent getting to Ragnaros and we have 760 hours that Conquest has been raiding Molten core. 
<br />

<br />
Now in that 760 hours, we have exactly 4. Yes FOUR poeple who have a full set of gear. Everyone else in the guild still needs one more pieces of gear. So rougly 36 others (we raid with pretty much same poeple everyday) in 760 hours of raiding do not even have a full set of gear. 
<br />

<br />
On our server we have someone ranked 13. He has been pvp'ing since honor was intruduced 10 weeks ago. He will most likely hit rank 14 today after servers come up. If he did not spend ATLEAST 760 hours pvp'ing in 10 weeks then it is completely unfair. I say ATLEAST because it has taken 40 poeple 760 hours of playing TOGETHER and only 4 of them have accomplished what this SOLO person did in only 10 weeks. 
<br />

<br />
I was the first person to finish off my set and it happened 4 weeks ago. At that rate of finishing off 4 poeple every 4 weeks with 36 poeple still left to finish off. So roughly 1 person per week, which remember is 8 hours. So we can add another 8*36 hours to our 760. That gives us 288+760 = 1048 hours. In my opinion for the current system to be fair. It should take a single person pvp'ing for 1,048 hours in order to reach rank 14. Anything less and raiding becomes not as profitable as pvp'ing. Human nature will dictate that we will take the path of least resistance which means raiding guilds will start to become pvp guilds and there will be no point to future content. 
<br />

<br />
Let me sum all this up for those of you who skipped to the bottom. It has taken 760 hours of raiding and will take another 288 hours more in order to gear up 40 poeple. That does NOT mean one person is geared up every ~26 hours of raiding. It means it takes ONE single person 1,048 hours of raiding to gear up completely. Anything less than that and you are screwing over the poeple who helped you get the gear. Conquest is more or less recognized as one of the top raiding guilds in WoW and I would say our proficiency at raiding is a lot higher than most other guilds. As such average Joe in a raiding guild will take even longer than 1,048 hours to gear up. 
<br />

<br />
If ANYONE can pvp for less than 1,048 hours and get full epic gear as a reward than it is completely unfair to guilds who raid. 
<br />

<br />
Zeem Madness </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

