			<tr>
				<td colspan="2" height="100%" valign="top"><span class="postbody">I personally think is a very bad decision.  Now all I have to do is make high warlord once and I get to keep the gear.  There is no reason for me to bother to try and maintain that rank now.
<br />

<br />
Even worse if you look at the PvP rewards, the melee based rewards are WAY better than the caster stuff.  So now we'll have rogues with a 2.00s 59.5dps  dagger that ambushes for something like 2500 and warriors running around mortal striking for ridiculous numbers.  What do casters get?  Considering your current staff probably already had around 20 sta on it then casters get the equivalent of 210 health.  And *maybe* 100 more mana.  The staff I have now already has more int than that PvP staff.  So for me it means giving up about 100 mana in exchange for 210 life.  Also it has +71 dmg, but keep in mind that's based on a 3 second cast time, so that means our most useful spells in PvP (instant cast) don't get that dmg boost.  On the other hand higher dmg weapons give melee instants a bigger boost.
<br />

<br />
Also keep in mind that I'm speaking of group PvP here.  Dueling is a whole different world and doesn't really have any bearing on how group PvP plays out.
<br />

<br />
It seems to me that melee keeps getting more and more dmg while casters get a little more life and mana.  I hope blizzard sees this flaw and steps up the bounty for casters.  We're going to be left behind soon.
<br />

<br />
If you make high warlord and maintain it then you deserve to be able to do those kind of things, but now all you have to do is get it once. Guess what?  It's going to be a lot easier to do now, since once the best people on the server already have it, there's no need for them to compete anymore.</span><br /><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
