			<tr>
				<td colspan="2" height="100%" valign="top"><span class="postbody">PvP Ranks are going to be the new "AA", I think.
<br />

<br />
Grind grind grind in PvP until you get rank 14, buy all your uber gear, go back to PvE raiding.
<br />

<br />
The min/maxers who don't really dig PvP but want the e-peen gear will just PvP up until they can get the gear and then go back to BWL or whatever.
<br />

<br />
Even if blizzard adjusts the curve so that only, say, 5% of a server's population can be rank 14 - I have a feeling that 5% will see quite a bit of turnover.  
<br />

<br />
And turnover at the Rank 14 position just accelerates the rate at which the purple melee epics enter the world.   Which means, as Vova pointed out, PvE mudflation will have to increase dramatically as well.
<br />

<br />
Which leads to a forced progression of content as now BWL and whatever is after that will *require* high-end MC loot, etc. etc. etc.  because they now have to balance the PvE encounters around everyone having rank 14 PvP loot - because all you have to do is get rank 14 once, and then stop PvPing until they release an expansion and you have to grind back to rank 21 or whatever....
<br />

<br />
Lame.</span><br /><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
