				<td colspan="2" height="100%" valign="top"><span class="postbody">Good change in a business sense, bad change for the game.  Casual gamers are going to be left even further behind now that those with more time can gear up without raiding.  There will be even LESS incentive for guilds to raid high end content.  
<br />

<br />
This change makes WOW  a first person shooter and not a fantasy role-playing game.
<br />

<br />
It also changes the very nature of the game - the core abilities of many classes (sheep, fear, etc.) are no longer viable in PVP - the game changes from knowledge of how to use your abilities to your ability to out guess your opponent.  That's fine, but it isn't the way the game was orignially designed.</span><br /><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
